	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1007124325990><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1999&mid=1007124325990>RE: Good Spare?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1999&mid=1007124325990#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=102727><span id= >AMPMagic</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 30th 7:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>This is how it works.<br><br>Magic Resistance is used to resist magic (all harmful magic, and has been know to block area affect spells cast by allies that should hurt you)<br>Now lets say you are like me 50 MR and 94 CR that means when a mob casts a cold based spell I will have a chance to resist it, If I dont and it hits me I will reduce the effect. I love fighting wizzies that use alot of cold based spells in combat, be them in duel every time!<br>MR also reduces duration of a spell effect. <br>So MR is important to have, and its best to get the other resists (focus in the one your class/race faces alot)<br>I know many pallies prefer DR cuase of the heavy contact from undead. I as a Ranger find myself getting hit with every Ice spell in the book. (side note with 94 CR the most powerful ice spell I have been hit with hits for 15dmg hehe)(hits my buddies alot more harder)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
