	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101830387299079><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1999&mid=101830387299079>RE: Good Spare?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1999&mid=101830387299079#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117647><span id= >Amneth</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>38 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 8th 6:16 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hrmm.<br><br>This is pretty much incorrect. MR is figured seperately from fr/cr/pr/dr. It is not additive. When you get into a fight with a caster though, its always good to have your mr up as high as possible given that alot of the general spells are resisted off of MR. however the only time a spell will use two resists of this sort is a spell that has multiple effects. So for instance, most nukes are off of just one resist. <br><br>Even in these cases (somewhat rare) each resist is rolled seperately, the two numbers are not added together.<br><br>AFAIK<br><br>-Amneth<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
